# Machine Learning Pipelines

This folder contains comprehensive Jupyter notebooks implementing supervised machine learning models to classify molecular crystal properties from descriptor data.

Models included:
- Decision Trees with hyperparameter tuning and evaluation.
- Feature Importance analysis for model interpretability.
- Logistic Regression classification pipelines.
- Random Forest ensemble models.
- Support Vector Machines (SVM) with advanced grid search for optimization.

Workflows demonstrate data balancing, train-test splits, model tuning, validation metrics, confusion matrix visualization, and model saving for later reuse.

## Usage

Run notebooks in order to replicate modeling experiments. Data preprocessing should be done beforehand. GridSearchCV is used for hyperparameter tuning.

## Dependencies

- Python 3.x
- pandas
- numpy
- scikit-learn
- matplotlib
- joblib (for model saving)
- jupyter/notebook environment
